<br>
<br>
This vegan soup is so flavourful you’ll want to keep a container tucked in the fridge at all times. To speed up the cooking process, be sure to have all of your veggies prepped and chopped before you begin cooking.</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>Ingredients</b>
<br><div class="mobileAdPlacement"></div>
<ul><li> ¼ cup extra virgin olive oil </li><li> 1 medium onion, chopped </li><li>2 carrots, peeled and chopped</li><li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li><li>2 tsp. ground cumin</li><li>1 sprig thyme leaves</li><li>1 28-oz. can crushed tomatoes</li><li>1 cup brown or green lentils, picked over and rinsed</li><li>4 cups chicken or vegetable stock</li><li>2 cups water</li><li>1 teaspoon kosher salt</li><li>Fresh ground pepper</li><li>1 cup chopped kale or baby spinach</li><li>Juice of ½ lemon</li></ul><br>
<b>Preparation time:</b> 20 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Cook time:</b> 45 minutes<br><br>
<b>Steps:</b>
<br><div class="teadsAdPlacement"></div>
1. Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven or pot set over medium heat. Once the oil is warm and shimmering, add the onion and carrot and cook, stirring often, until the onion has soft and translucent, about 5 minutes. <br>
2. Add the garlic, cumin, and thyme. Cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Pour in the tomatoes and cook for a few more minutes, stirring often, in order to enhance their flavour. <br>
3. Add the lentils, broth and water to the pot, along with one teaspoon salt; season with freshly ground black pepper. Bring the mixture to a boil, then partially cover the pot and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook for 30 minutes, or until the lentils are tender but still hold their shape. <br>
4. Add the kale to the pot and cook for 5 more minutes, or until the greens have wilted slightly.
5. Remove the pot from heat and stir in the juice of half of a lemon. Taste and season with more salt, pepper and/or lemon juice until you reach the desired flavour. Serve hot.
